I married you because I loved you.

3
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:09,595
I've worked with him side-by-side
all this time.

4
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:13,190
How could I have not known he was
bribing this woman from city council?

5
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:15,868
I spoke with Renee Wheeler.
I know about the affair.

6
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:20,517
Sixteen years is a long time to be paying
palimony. Unless there was a child.

7
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:24,474
I'm talking too much. I get nervous,
start talking, and nothing shuts me up.

8
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:26,949
If you came to the judge
with documentation...

9
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,515
-...the DA would drop the charges.
-Mom.

10
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:30,954
What are you doing here?

11
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:54,196
What is the point of living in Southern
California if it's gonna be this cold?

12
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:57,238
Fifty degrees in December, Cal.
That ain't cold.

13
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,868
Well, my blood
must have gotten thinner.

14
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:02,156
Or you got ice in your veins.

15
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:07,029
This time next year...

16
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:10,552
...I could be spending the holidays
behind bars.

17
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,631
Now, that gives me a chill.

18
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:15,155
Don't know how you feel about it.

19
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:19,393
Warm and fuzzy. How do you think
it makes me feel, Sandy?

20
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:22,473
What the hell else can I do?

21
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:25,234
You can come forward.
Trial's right around the corner.

22
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:29,951
Renee's gonna plead the Fifth,
and when she does, you're sunk.

23
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,918
Unless you tell the truth.

24
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:34,800
I can't. You know I can't.

25
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:37,269
-What about the child?
-Which child?

26
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,271
Lindsay?

27
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:43,113
How do you know her name?

28
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,759
Yeah.

29
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:49,559
-What happens to her?
-Spare me.

30
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:53,349
You're not trying to protect Lindsay.
You're trying to protect yourself...

31
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:57,349
...because you know once you come
clean, you'll get what's coming to you.

32
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:02,397
But facing Kirsten and Julie
has got to be better than going to jail.

33
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,156
Kirsten, maybe.

34
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:07,197
Not Julie.

35
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:10,796
Well, then this is it.

36
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,190
I'm done, and so are you.

37
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,316
Happy holidays.

38
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:41,438
Mother? Did you not clean out
last year's menorah?

39
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:43,636
This shammash
is looking a little bit waxy.

40
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:47,071
-Seth, sorry. I'll get right on that.
-A little help here, please?

41
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,515
Thanks, Mom.
We can't afford to cut any corners.

42
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:54,077
If my sense of the cultural Zeitgeist
is accurate, and I do believe it is...

43
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:57,716
...this year, Chrismukkah sweeps
the nation, okay, people?

44
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:00,474
Ryan, it's so nice to have someone
to help around the house.

45
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:05,475
You're right, it is, which is why I've
created a Chrismukkah work wheel...

46
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:08,359
...so that everybody understands
his or her holiday duties.

47
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,796
-You're kidding.
-Does it look like it?

48
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,355
-Let me guess your job.
-I'm supervising, smartass.

49
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:20,109
-Well, that's big of you.
-I'm also overseeing merchandising.

50
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,554
T -shirts, mugs, and...

51
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:24,996
...I'm penning a Chrismukkah hymn
set to Death Cab's "A Lack of Color. "

52
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:27,668
-All the makings of a classic.
-ls Death Cab a band?

53
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:31,350
Around we go on the wheel, and, Mom,
you're in charge of interior decor.

54
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:34,632
That's gonna mean trimmings,
ornaments, frosting of the windows.

55
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,791
Don't know, don't care.
Just make it classy.

56
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,515
I'll do my best. I've invited the Nichols,
or the Cooper-Nichols.

57
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,915
-Whatever they're called.
-They are gentiles.

58
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,439
A whole slew of them at that.

59
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:47,757
Let's put our heads together,
do some serious Jew-cruitment. Ryan?

60
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,632
Think you can rope in some Hebrews?

61
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,957
-Blond hair, blue eyes. I'm a natural.
-Fair point, Aryan friend.

62
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:56,669
Okay, where are we gonna find
some Jews in Orange County?

63
00:03:56,880 --> 00:04:01,237
Father! I have just discovered
the ideal job for you this Chrismukkah.

64
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,955
Chrismukkah. Leave me out of it.

65
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,676
-Oy, humbug.
-Oy, humbug.

66
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,233
Your dad seemed pretty upset.

67
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,231
You know my dad and the holidays.

68
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,709
He likes a slow build.
Doesn't wanna peak too soon.

69
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:50,269
It's a long holiday.
You gotta pace yourself.

70
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:54,035
Hey. It's a marathon of presents,
not a race.

71
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:57,590
To get through this holiday season,
you must set a pace.

72
00:04:57,760 --> 00:05:00,433
Those are good lyrics for the song.
Do you have a pen?

73
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:03,837
-You're not really writing a song?
-For Chrismukkah to go global...

74
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,912
...we need an anthem.
I'm thinking little JoJo can record it.

75
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,475
While spreading Chrismukkah,
you inviting Alex?

76
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,318
I did. She's away with her folks.

77
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,550
Probably at some Club Med tattoo parlor.

78
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,392
What about you? Is Lindsay around?

79
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,556
-Y eah. I think she is.
-Gonna invite her?

80
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,115
I can't. I mean, it's kind of a big step.

81
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,436
And with Marissa there,
it'd be weird for her.

82
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,989
Marissa won't be there.
My mom drew a seating chart.

83
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,509
-She said she'll be with her dad.
-Really?

84
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,718
We just got things to a good place,
got a little mystery back.

85
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:34,189
Inviting her for the holidays
might be rushing it.

86
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:37,989
Then don't do it, man. Do not do it.
Last thing you wanna do is rush things.

87
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:42,630
-What are you doing? We'll be late.
-Sorry.

88
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,353
Sure we're not rushing things?

89
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:54,230
Well, you know, we were married
for 1 7 years, so....

90
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,719
It's just been....

91
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,757
It's been so long since we've done this.

92
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:00,832
Well, it's like--
It's like riding a bike.

93
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:03,315
An incredibly toned...

94
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:07,359
...and, you know,
evenly tanned and limber bike.

95
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:12,834
You know, with a really sharp mind
and incredible sense of....

96
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:16,198
Of interior design.

97
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:21,033
Oh, God, slow down. I'm sorry.

98
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:28,476
It's just-- Does this count as--?
As adultery?

99
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:31,871
You know, cheating on your husband
with your ex-husband?

100
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,679
Technically, I think....

101
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:37,035
It does, yeah.

102
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:40,034
Okay, sorry.

103
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,679
Let's just-- Okay.

104
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,796
-What?
-Caleb and I aren't getting along.

105
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:45,916
He hasn't touched me in months.

106
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,911
He's probably going to jail.

107
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:51,470
Well, I think it's wonderful
how maturely you're handling it all.

108
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,517
I don't hear you complaining.

109
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,796
Well, do you wanna stop?

110
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,277
No.

111
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,231
Thanks for coming
on such short notice.

112
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,391
I don't have much
of a lunch break, so....

113
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,873
-Why meet here?
-I've run out of places to go.

114
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:19,919
I've had so many secret meetings lately,
I feel like I'm in an Oliver Stone movie.

115
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:24,593
Look, I know you feel that if you
come forward you'll lose your daughter.

116
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,079
You may lose her either way.

117
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:30,511
The DA's sure Caleb was bribing
someone in the councilman's office.

118
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,994
Bribing you.

119
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,515
Unless somebody testifies differently...

120
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,956
...they have enough evidence
to send you to jail.

121
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:44,199
How do I tell my daughter
that I've been lying to her her whole life?

122
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:47,591
Inventing a father she never had.
Keeping her from meeting her family.

123
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,438
Maybe it's time she met him.

124
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,318
Maybe it's time to stop lying.

125
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:54,318
Caleb won't come forward.
I can't.

126
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,429
You're our last hope.

127
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:01,155
I'm sorry.

128
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,590
-Hey.
-Hey.

129
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,269
-You gonna study all Christmas break?
-I hope so.

130
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:15,398
Keep me distracted from remembering
it's actually Christmas.

131
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,913
Not a fan of the holidays?

132
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,833
-Who is?
-Well, Seth, actually.

133
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,719
He's even invented his own
super-holiday. Chrismukkah.

134
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,198
-Chrismukkah?
-Yeah.

135
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:28,710
Well, that's cute.

136
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:31,030
I guess. It's....

137
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:35,512
It's eight days of gifts, followed
by one day of many, many gifts.

138
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:38,319
We eat Chinese food
and watch Christmas movies.

139
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,391
Though, last year,
we watched Over the Top.

140
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:43,991
-Well, a classic any time of year.
-That's what I'm saying.

141
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:50,592
Me and my mom,
we stopped even buying a tree.

142
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:54,799
It always just looked so sad
with just two gifts under it.

143
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:58,832
When I was little...

144
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:02,995
...all my friends were waiting
for something from Santa...

145
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:07,392
...and I was just hoping...

146
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,276
...for something...

147
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:14,518
...anything, from my dad.

148
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:17,479
-Still waiting?
-Not anymore.

149
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:23,794
Every kid grows up,
stops believing in Santa.

150
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,360
I stopped believing in my dad...

151
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:30,478
...and there's no pine needles
to clean up.

152
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,477
So....

153
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:38,430
Disappointed by your family
over the holidays. I've been there.

154
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,680
So do what I did.

155
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:44,229
Find another family to spend them with.

156
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,677
Come over.

157
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,432
Come over for Chrismukkah?

158
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,990
It'd be better if you were Jewish.

159
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,873
There's a ratio issue, but it'll be fun.

160
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,672
-Seth will keep you very distracted.
-Can we watch Over the Top?

161
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:01,196
I could watch that movie
1 00 times and never get sick of it.

162
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:06,477
Where's Zach?
I'm not used to seeing you without him.

163
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:09,148
He left early for Christmas in Cabo
with his fam.

164
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,356
He's been gone a day,
and I miss him already.

165
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:14,838
DJ's in Sacramento
with his family for two weeks.

166
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,274
I miss him too.

167
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:19,790
Well, this should be a fun break.
Me, you, Caleb and my step-monster.

168
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,234
Should be one for the ages.

169
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,799
We could spike the eggnog.

170
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,998
-Coop.
-Kidding. Kind of.

171
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,470
Actually, not really.

172
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:32,637
This sucks.
Last year the holidays were so much fun.

173
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:36,230
Yeah. I got rejected by Cohen
in a Wonder Woman costume...

174
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:37,992
...and you got caught shoplifting.

175
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,839
-Yeah. It was memorable, though.
-I guess it was.

176
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:43,635
Hey, can I get a large coffee, please?
Thanks.

177
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,319
Hey, guys.
Merry Chrismukkah.

178
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,034
-Don't remind us.
-Forgot about your little holiday.

179
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:52,711
Okay. My color-coded holiday
alert system is detecting you two.

180
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,472
You're taupe. Come on.

181
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:57,598
That's a very dangerously low level
of holiday cheer.

182
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,756
I don't know what you're talking about.

183
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:02,599
I am looking forward to dinner
with my stepmom...

184
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:06,110
-...face down in her Christmas ham.
-I can't wait to be on Dad's boat...

185
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:08,669
...and hear him talk
about how much he misses Hailey.

186
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,798
Wait a second, guys.
Summer. Marissa.

187
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:15,311
On behalf of Jesus
and Judah Maccabee and the Cohens...

188
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,631
...I'd like to cordially invite you both,
and your dad, Marissa...

189
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,268
...but not yours,
because he scares and hates me...

190
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:25,593
...to come celebrate a little holiday
I like to call Chrismukkah.

191
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:30,788
It's also sort of my way of apologizing
for the whole SnO.C. debacle.

192
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,798
-Sure, why not?
-Okay, whatever.

193
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:36,197
Hey. Somebody just went
from taupe to putty.

194
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:40,149
Kirsten, are you ready
for the investors meeting?

195
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:44,757
Thanks. I was, and I attended
the meeting two hours ago.

196
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:47,718
What? Two hours?

197
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:52,511
My new assistant is constantly putting
the wrong numbers into my BlackBerry.

198
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,238
I tried to reach you all morning.

199
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,868
Well, my battery must have died.

200
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:00,198
Or not.

201
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,715
That's so funny.
That's Jimmy's favorite song.

202
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:04,672
Is it? I forgot.

203
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,279
That's why you got it.

204
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,954
I got "Hungry Like the Wolf. "
He got "The Hustle. "

205
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,549
-I was there when you picked them out.
-lt is Jimmy.

206
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:15,474
Nothing gets by you, Kirsten.
You've got a memory like an elephant.

207
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,075
-You gonna answer it?
-No. It's just Jimmy.

208
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:21,078
-Thought you were getting along.
-Why do you say that?

209
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:24,511
Last week when you said you and Jimmy
were getting along really well.

210
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:28,599
-You okay? You seem frazzled.
-Yeah, well, you know....

211
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:31,593
I didn't get a chance to blow my hair out
this morning, so....

212
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,518
I said frazzled.

213
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,230
Not frizzy.

214
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:40,759
-Hey, is dinner ready yet?
-No. Your dad's at the grill.

215
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,509
I'm famished.
All this planning for the big day.

216
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,954
Taking it out of you, huh?

217
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:49,715
Hey. Ye of little faith.
Trust those of mixed faith.

218
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:52,030
Okay, this year,
it's gonna be off the charts.

219
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,760
-It's gonna be Cochise.
-What's Cochise?

220
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:58,708
Highest level of holiday cheer
on my color-coded holiday alert system.

221
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:01,110
-Cochise is a color?
-It's in the beige family.

222
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:04,033
-Couldn't go with blue?
-Listen, it's gonna be awesome.

223
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,316
Especially now Marissa
and Summer are coming--

224
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,391
Whoa, I thought
Marissa was with her dad.

225
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,238
She was,
but she was bummed about it.

226
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,992
Since you're not inviting Lindsay--

227
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,156
Except I did invite Lindsay.

228
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:17,995
-That's awkward.
-Seth. What am I gonna do?

229
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:20,469
They can't hang out together.
It's too weird.

230
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:22,079
-I agree.
-Not helping.

231
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:25,078
Oh, God, what if it's starting?

232
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,157
-What if what?
-Chrismukkah backlash.

233
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,038
Is it getting too big and commercial?

234
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,754
-Guess I'm done studying.
-I knew this would happen.

235
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:35,151
It starts out
as this really cool cult holiday...

236
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,038
...flying beneath the cultural radar.

237
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:40,397
Then, all of a sudden, it crosses over,
and there's too much pressure.

238
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:42,471
Can it really be the next Thanksgiving?

239
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:44,710
-Can it top Halloween?
-This is off topic.

240
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:47,229
The government will ask me
to create new holidays.

241
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:50,039
Like East-over or Kwanzaa-shanah?
Can't let it happen.

242
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:53,351
-Hey, guys.
-Can't talk now. We have an emergency.

243
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:56,876
-What's going on?
